<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="283" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,438,463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Description</emphasis>
. Head. Face (
<figureCitation box="[493,561,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[546,561,439,463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) with only slightly exposed on lower ½ in lateral view, sparse black and short setae dorsally; remaining area and oral border with abundant long macrosetae directed anteriorly and ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[159,227,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,227,511,535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Postpedicel of antenna as long as scape and pedicel combined (
<figureCitation box="[964,1034,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[1017,1034,511,535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); scape 
<number box="[1125,1160,510,535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as pedicel (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,229,547,571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); stylus slightly longer than scape and pedicel; apex of stylus bare (
<figureCitation box="[985,1054,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[1037,1054,547,571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Thorax. Tumid, postsutural dorsocentral macrosetae, notopleural, supraalar and postalar macrosetae strong; anatergal setae absent; scutellum tumid as the thorax and coxae, without rim on posterior border; 
<number box="[1315,1329,619,643]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
scutellar macrosetae on posterior border, sparse, fine, short setae on disc and border; pleura asetose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[275,342,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[326,342,690,715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Cell r 
<number box="[429,440,691,715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
closed before wing margin; stump vein supernumerary crossvein on R 
<number box="[1227,1235,705,719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
absent; R 
<number box="[1346,1354,705,719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
ending before the wing tip, and R 
<number box="[443,451,744,758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="5.0">5</number>
, after; m 
<number box="[555,567,730,754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="3.0">3</number>
cell closed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[269,335,768,793]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[322,335,768,792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Coxae gray; femora shining black; tibiae yellow, except for brown stripe anteriorly; tarsus light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" box="[199,868,840,865]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Abdomen. Vestiture as in notum; sides of all tergites setose.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Male terminalia. Angled 
<number box="[488,516,876,901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="45.0">45</number>
º with abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[715,783,876,901]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[224,1332,195,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[224,1359,195,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 1, Habitus, lateral view; 2, Head, frontal view; 3, Head, lateral view; 4, Antennae, lateral view; 5, Wing; Male terminalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: pp: postpedicel; ped: pedicel; scp: scape; sty: stylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229650/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[770,783,877,901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); epandrium flat ventrally, looks like goat hoof (
<figureCitation box="[1350,1421,876,901]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[1405,1421,877,901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandria broad and thick, subglobular on proximal 
<number box="[732,745,912,936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[755,770,912,936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
, attenuated distally and meeting in an acute tip (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1421,912,937]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Figs. 
<number box="[1378,1421,912,937]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">
6 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1391,1405,912,937]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">–</emphasis>
8
</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites globular on basal 
<number box="[517,530,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[539,554,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
, distal 
<number box="[643,653,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[663,679,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0">4</number>
flattened, elongate, with 
<number box="[981,1022,948,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">
3 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[995,1009,948,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">–</emphasis>
5
</number>
teeth or spines ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1422,948,973]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[1391,1422,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Median region of gonocoxite with round tumid protuberance with few short setae (
<figureCitation box="[1078,1228,984,1009]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Figs. 7, 8, 
<number box="[1197,1228,984,1008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite with 
<number box="[151,165,1021,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
conspicuous patches of long setae, 
<number box="[562,576,1021,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="1.0">1</number>
of scattered long, fine, yellow setae directed posteriorly and other with patch of dense long, golden setae directed to opposite side and crossing over hypandrium tip as golden belt (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Figs. 7, 8, 
<number box="[151,180,1093,1117]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); gonostylus long, flattened towards apex, with abundant short, fine setae and few macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[1282,1422,1092,1117]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Figs. 11, 12</figureCitation>
); gonostylus hidden in closed genitalia; hypandrium subglobose and subtriangular, with 
<number box="[1125,1139,1128,1152]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="3.0">3</number>
small tubercles on tip and patch of 
<number box="[251,279,1165,1189]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="12.0">12</number>
long, fine setae on each side, directed posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[861,1044,1164,1189]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">Figs. 7, 8, 9, 11</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus long, ending in 
<number box="[1364,1378,1165,1189]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
long tubes, ejaculatory apodeme thin and long, not expanded apically (
<figureCitation box="[886,970,1200,1225]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[262,1322,259,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[246,1335,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Male. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view; 7, Male terminalia, ventral view; 8, Male terminalia, ventral view; 9, Male terminalia, lateral view; 10, Inner margin of epandrium and subepandrial sclerite; 11, Hypandrium, gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral view; 12, gonocoxite and gonostylus; 13, Aedeagus and ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Abbreviations: aed: aedeagus; cerc: cercus; ej apod: ejaculatory apodeme; epand: epandrium; goncx: gonocoxite; gonst: gonostylus; hypd: hypandrium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229651/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[939,970,1200,1224]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,330,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Female terminalia. Ovipositor compressed, formed by segment VIII and the following (
<figureCitation box="[1199,1338,1236,1261]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,193,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[215,1373,193,1840]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 18. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Female. 14, Habitus, lateral view; 15, Ovipositor, lateral view; 16, Ovipositor, dorsal view; 17, Ovipositor, ventral view; 18, Genital fork and spermathecae. Abbreviations: ar: arms of genital fork; cap duct: capsular ducts; com duct: common duct; exp duct: expulsory ducts; cerc: cercus; f apod: furcal apodeme; spmth: spermathecae; stVIII: sternite VIII; tVII: tergite VII; tVIII: tergite VIII; tIX + X: tergite IX + X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229652/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Figs. 
<number box="[1264,1338,1237,1261]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="15.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="14.0">14–17</number>
</figureCitation>
); genital fork with long, thin arms, about 
<number box="[524,559,1272,1297]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times longer than base, base much wider than arms (
<figureCitation box="[1172,1258,1272,1297]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,193,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[215,1373,193,1840]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 18. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Female. 14, Habitus, lateral view; 15, Ovipositor, lateral view; 16, Ovipositor, dorsal view; 17, Ovipositor, ventral view; 18, Genital fork and spermathecae. Abbreviations: ar: arms of genital fork; cap duct: capsular ducts; com duct: common duct; exp duct: expulsory ducts; cerc: cercus; f apod: furcal apodeme; spmth: spermathecae; stVIII: sternite VIII; tVII: tergite VII; tVIII: tergite VIII; tIX + X: tergite IX + X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229652/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[1227,1258,1272,1296]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
); common duct long (
<figureCitation box="[220,307,1308,1333]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,193,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[215,1373,193,1840]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 18. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Female. 14, Habitus, lateral view; 15, Ovipositor, lateral view; 16, Ovipositor, dorsal view; 17, Ovipositor, ventral view; 18, Genital fork and spermathecae. Abbreviations: ar: arms of genital fork; cap duct: capsular ducts; com duct: common duct; exp duct: expulsory ducts; cerc: cercus; f apod: furcal apodeme; spmth: spermathecae; stVIII: sternite VIII; tVII: tergite VII; tVIII: tergite VIII; tIX + X: tergite IX + X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229652/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[276,307,1309,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[332,346,1309,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
expulsory and capsular ducts ending in 
<number box="[824,838,1309,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="2.0">2</number>
spherical capsules, as wide as the width tip of the apodeme of the furca (
<figureCitation box="[403,487,1344,1369]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,193,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[215,1373,193,1840]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 18. Papaverellus aureocingulatus Artigas &amp; Vieira gen. nov. et sp. nov. Female. 14, Habitus, lateral view; 15, Ovipositor, lateral view; 16, Ovipositor, dorsal view; 17, Ovipositor, ventral view; 18, Genital fork and spermathecae. Abbreviations: ar: arms of genital fork; cap duct: capsular ducts; com duct: common duct; exp duct: expulsory ducts; cerc: cercus; f apod: furcal apodeme; spmth: spermathecae; stVIII: sternite VIII; tVII: tergite VII; tVIII: tergite VIII; tIX + X: tergite IX + X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229652/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="283">
Fig. 
<number box="[456,487,1344,1368]" pageId="1" pageNumber="283" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
